5:40PM BST 28 Sep 2009
Stay-at-home Russians prefer the regions
The time when every Russian dreamt of moving to Moscow may be coming to an end, data from state-run pollster VTsIOM poll shows.
More people now believe that they can become richer or start their business more easily in the region where they live or elsewhere in the country, the poll said.
Forty-six pc of respondents believed that they could find their fortune in Moscow, down from 57pc a year earlier. While the number of those who said they could find a prosperous life in the regions has increased to 19pc, from 12pc last year.
The number of respondents saying they could find a suitable job in the capital rather than in the regions fell to 46pc, from 57pc last year.
